        .portfolio-bio
          h3 <bold>The Short Version</bold>
          p(class="special-p")
            | My name is Jamie Gobeille. A Full-stack Developer from Cincinnati, Ohio living in Nagoya, Japan with my beautiful, amazing wife. <div class= "heart">&#10084</div> <p class="heart-text">of all things code, Japan, and beer. I began coding in November of 2017 and haven't looked back.  
            | My wheelhouse includes mostly vanillaJS, CSS, and HTML to create beautiful websites and web applications. I am extremely passionate about learning new web technologies and sharing what I know to the community.
            | I have worked with both businesses and charities to design their website and craft content, promotional items, and solutions suited to their needs.
                        
            |<bold>**Shameless Plug**</bold> I also like to write <a class ="link" href="https://medium.com/@jamiegobeille">articles</a> about JavaScript and Web Development</p>
          
          h3 <bold>The Long Version</bold>
          p  
            | ...Over the past couple of years code has become an integral part of my life. It has influenced me in ways I never thought it would. It was the first time I felt extremely proud of my work accomplishments. I was given a creative outlet to pursue thoughts and ideas in my head that I didn't think I could ever do on my own. Learning to code influenced me in my daily life as well. It taught me to be organized and how to breakdown seemingly massive problems into small manageable bites.
            | Since learning to code I have been lucky enough to work some businesses craft solutions tailored to their needs such as making a website and shopify e-commerce store for one client and helping maintain a charities website,making new content, and eventually making a custom e-commerce store in the future.
 
          p
            | When I am not working on projects, I am actively reaching out and helping students on Team Treehouse's Fullstack Tech Degree Slack channel where I am designated "Slack Champion". I also watch a lot of popular coding you tube channels such as:
            ul(class="youtube-channels")
